## My Recommendation

Keep these **five services** from the beginning:

1. **Admin Web App** (React)
2. **Farmer Mobile App** (Flutter)
3. **Node.js Backend** (REST API, WebSocket, Business Logic)
4. **Master Service** (Raspberry Pi - HTTP/WebSocket + Modbus TCP Client)
5. **Slave Firmware** (ESP32 - Modbus TCP Server)

This separation gives you a clean, scalable architecture. As you move from a local WiFi MVP to a cloud-connected production system (MQTT, RS485, remote deployments), each component can evolve independently without requiring major changes to the rest of the system.
